Old Mutual Is Urged to Sell U.K. Insurance, Mail on Sunday Says

-- B y   E d u a r d   G i s m a t u l l i n
-- 
2011-03-13T13:45:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/old-mutual-is-urged-to-sell-u-k-insurance-mail-on-sunday-says.html
  Old Mutual Plc (OML)  has been urged by
shareholder Cevian Capital AB to sell its U.K. life insurance
business to simplify operations and boost profit, the Mail on
Sunday  reported , citing Martin Oliw, a partner at Cevian.  The British life insurance unit could be sold for as much
as 2 billion pounds ($3.2 billion), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduard Gismatullin in London at 
 egismatullin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Will Kennedy  at 
 wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  